{
  "text": "Coherent and subsequent incoherent growth has been proposed for growth of ringwoodite lamellae in Yamato 791384 chondrite [CITATION_1] . It is argued that a thin layer of coherent ringwoodite followed by a thicker layer of incoherent ringwoodite formed within $ 4 s to produce the 23 mm wide ringwoodite zone observed [CITATION_2] .",
